Description: The Flight into Egypt; night scene with the Virgin and Child at centre riding on an donkey towards left, St Joseph seen from behind and walking beside them at right, an angel at left holding the ass's bridle and leading the way, two other angels in clouds above; after Peter Paul Rubens Engraving
Producer name: Print made by: Cornelis Galle the Younger (Galle, Cornelis II)
Curator's comments: For a drawing by Rubens see Gg,2.234.
Bibliographic references: Schneevoogt 1873 / Catalogue des estampes gravées d'après P.P.Rubens (24.103)
